related_questions.question: Are spiny lobsters good to eat?
related_questions.snippet: How to eat it. As we mentioned, spiny lobster can thrown in just about anything – macaroni and cheese, an omelette, gumbo – and it tastes delicious. It's not far off from the taste of a crawfish, so its versatility in working within just about any recipe is its strong point.

related_questions.question: Is spiny lobster better than maine lobster?
related_questions.snippet: The Spiny Lobster has a sweeter flavor profile than its counterpart, the Maine Lobster. It also has more meat — generally around 25% more per pound. And unlike Maine Lobsters, they don't have claws, and instead use their spine and tail as their sources of defense.
